  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LIFE: Food Security &amp; Entrepreneurship</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Geographically, Northern and Central river belt region of Bangladesh are flood plain, formed through siltation carried by three mighty rivers namely Padma, Jamuna, Brahmaputra from upstream. Historically, the regions affected by flood every year and local ecosystems are very much fragile. However, climate change triggered disasters such as flood, river bank erosion, siltation, drought, cold wave, dense fog, heat wave, salinity intrusion  all are contributing to reduce agriculture production and in some cases destroying whole production and there by hampering the overall food security of the area.

The ultimate goal of this project is to make communities more resilient to adverse effect of climate change and enhance food security by adapting sustainable livelihood options. The LIFEprogramme has been designed to achieve the goal by making communities more resilient to climate shocks while ensuring food security, livelihood and market linkage development with Private sector. To ensure food security the programme will contribute in increasingthe production agricultural crops and Homestead gardening, ensure sustainable livelihood through adopting alternative IGA training and input support and vocational skills developing of youths for creating better employment opportunities.

Considering the local context, three non-government development organizations grouped together and designed the project. Having long-standing experience in the selected areas,Gana Unnayan Kendra (GUK) implement the project in Gaibandha, Gono Kalyan Sangstha-GKS in Sirajgonj and Shariatpur Development Society (SDS) in Shariatpur district.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GKS - Gono Kalyan Sangstha</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gono Kalyan Sangstha (GKS) is one of the most renowned non-governmental development organization located in Sirajgonj district. It#s a people led organization that was established locally in 1985 by a group of committed people under the  leadership of Khondaker Selim Jahangir with a view to empower disadvantaged poor people and destitute specially women, youth and children through improving their socio-economic status and reducing vulnerability from all aspects. GKS has a long experience in the field of disaster preparedness, emergency relief &lt;(&gt;&amp;&lt;)&gt; rehabilitation and reconstruction project. GKS implemented #Preparedness for Effective Emergency Response Project (PEER)# in collaboration with Union, Upazila &lt;(&gt;&amp;&lt;)&gt; District level Disaster Management Committees.

Since GKS has long experience in implementing donor funded project that is why the organization is very much conscious and responsive to the donor requirements. From the beginning to end of any emergency response GKS strongly maintain proper planning, coordination, reporting, monitoring and documentation of whole process and able submit the required information and reports based on the donor requirements. GKS gives emphasise on learning doing and clearly understands when, where and on what context humanitarian response is required as well asable to find the scope of humanitarian response that will reduce the immediate sufferings of affected populations.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
